@startuml MatchMonitorGroupBetting_CompleteFlow
!theme plain
title Match Monitor Group Betting - Complete & Clean Flow

start

:Processing Complete (Round 1 & 2);
note right
    MatchProcesses[] contains all results:
    - Round 1 results
    - Round 2 results (if any)
    
    Each item in MatchProcesses:
    - MatchInfo (match details)
    - RoundNumber (1 or 2)
    - CompleteMatches[] (fraud groups found)
    - ReprocessMatches[] (items for next round)
end note

partition "=== MERGE RESULTS ===" {
    :Extract Complete Matches;
    note right
        var mergeMatchComplete = MatchProcesses?
            .Where(x => x.CompleteMatches.IsNotNullOrEmpty())
            .SelectMany(x => x.CompleteMatches)
        
        This gets all CompleteMatches from:
        - All Round 1 results
        - All Round 2 results
        
        Flattens nested structure to single list
    end note
    
    :Group By TransIDList;
    note right
        .GroupBy(item => item.TransIDList)
        
        Purpose: Remove duplicates
        
        Example:
        Round 1: TransIDList = "101,102,103"
        Round 2: TransIDList = "101,102,103" (same group)
        → Group them together, keep only one
        
        Why duplicates?
        - Same fraud pattern found in both rounds
        - Overlapping detection
        - Refinement resulted in same group
    end note
    
    :Assign Sequential GroupID;
    note right
        .Select((group, index) => {
            var result = group.First();  // Take first from group
            result.GroupId = index + 1;  // Assign 1, 2, 3, ...
            return result;
        })
        
        Example:
        Group 1: TransIDList="101,102,103" → GroupID = 1
        Group 2: TransIDList="104,105" → GroupID = 2
        Group 3: TransIDList="106,107,108,109" → GroupID = 3
        
        Benefits:
        - Clean, sequential IDs
        - Easy to understand
        - No gaps in sequence
    end note
    
    :Merged Results Ready;
    note right
        Structure: IEnumerable<MatchCompleteRuleGroupBettingEntity>
        
        Example:
        [
            {
                GroupId: 1,
                TransIDList: "101,102,103",
                CustIDList: "user1,user2,user3",
                AssociationType: "Device",
                TotalAmount: 300.00,
                TotalOdds: 5.85,
                TicketCount: 3,
                CustCount: 3
            },
            {
                GroupId: 2,
                TransIDList: "104,105",
                CustIDList: "user4,user5",
                AssociationType: "IP,3Matches",
                TotalAmount: 200.00,
                TotalOdds: 4.10,
                TicketCount: 2,
                CustCount: 2
            },
            ...
        ]
    end note
}

if (mergeMatchComplete.IsNotNullOrEmpty()?) then (yes)

    partition "=== CREATE COMPLETE PARAMETER ===" {
        :Build MatchCompleteRuleGroupBettingParameterModel;
        note right
            var para = new MatchCompleteRuleGroupBettingParameterModel
            {
                IsLive = IsLive,
                MatchInfo = MatchStaging,
                MaxSequenceID = maxSequenceID,
                TransGroupJson = JsonConvert.SerializeObject(mergeMatchComplete)
            };
            
            Fields:
            -------
            IsLive: true/false (Live or Non-Live)
            
            MatchInfo: {
                MatchID: 987654,
                ScoreDiff: "0-0",
                BettypeID: 1,
                BetID: "AH-0.5",
                Betteam: "H",
                SportType: 1
            }
            
            MaxSequenceID: 12346678
            
            TransGroupJson: JSON string of merged groups
            (See merged results structure above)
        end note
        
        :Parameter Model Ready;
    }
    
    partition "=== CALL COMPLETE SP ===" {
        :CompleteTransRuleGroupBetting(para);
        
        :Database SP Execution;
        note right
            Database: CTS_DataCenter (MySQL)
            SP: CTS_MatchMonitor_RuleGroupBetting_Complete
            
            Input Parameters:
            -----------------
            @IsLive = 1
            @MatchInfo = '{
                "MatchID": 987654,
                "ScoreDiff": "0-0",
                "BettypeID": 1,
                ...
            }'
            @MaxSequenceID = 12346678
            @TransGroupJson = '[
                {
                    "GroupId": 1,
                    "TransIDList": "101,102,103",
                    ...
                },
                ...
            ]'
        end note
        
        partition "SP Logic" {
            :Parse Input JSON;
            note right
                -- Parse MatchInfo
                SELECT @MatchID = JSON_VALUE(@MatchInfo, '$.MatchID');
                SELECT @ScoreDiff = JSON_VALUE(@MatchInfo, '$.ScoreDiff');
                SELECT @BettypeID = JSON_VALUE(@MatchInfo, '$.BettypeID');
                ... etc
                
                -- Parse TransGroupJson into temp table
                CREATE TEMPORARY TABLE TempCompleteGroups AS
                SELECT 
                    GroupId,
                    TransIDList,
                    CustIDList,
                    AssociationType,
                    TotalAmount,
                    TotalOdds,
                    TicketCount,
                    CustCount
                FROM JSON_TABLE(@TransGroupJson, '$[*]'
                    COLUMNS (
                        GroupId INT PATH '$.GroupId',
                        TransIDList TEXT PATH '$.TransIDList',
                        CustIDList TEXT PATH '$.CustIDList',
                        AssociationType VARCHAR(100) PATH '$.AssociationType',
                        TotalAmount DECIMAL(18,2) PATH '$.TotalAmount',
                        TotalOdds DECIMAL(10,3) PATH '$.TotalOdds',
                        TicketCount INT PATH '$.TicketCount',
                        CustCount INT PATH '$.CustCount'
                    )
                ) AS jt;
            end note
            
            :Calculate Rule Scores;
            note right
                -- Calculate fraud score for each group
                ALTER TABLE TempCompleteGroups 
                ADD COLUMN RuleScore DECIMAL(10,4);
                
                UPDATE TempCompleteGroups
                SET RuleScore = CalculateRuleScore(
                    TotalAmount,
                    TotalOdds,
                    CustCount,
                    TicketCount,
                    AssociationType
                );
                
                CalculateRuleScore() Logic:
                --------------------------
                Base Score = 50
                + Amount Factor: (TotalAmount / 1000) * 10
                + Customer Factor: CustCount * 5
                + Odds Factor: (TotalOdds - 2.0) * 3
                + Association Type Bonus:
                  - "Device": +20
                  - "Device,IP": +30
                  - "Device,IP,3Matches": +40
                  - "AI": +25
                
                Max Score = 100
                Min Score = 0
                
                High Score = High Fraud Probability
            end note
            
            :Insert Results;
            note right
                INSERT INTO CTSMatchMonitorRuleGroupBetting (
                    MatchID,
                    GroupID,
                    TransIDList,
                    CustIDList,
                    AssociationType,
                    TotalAmount,
                    TotalOdds,
                    TicketCount,
                    CustCount,
                    DetectionType,
                    RuleScore,
                    BettypeID,
                    BetID,
                    Betteam,
                    ScoreDiff,
                    SportType,
                    IsLive,
                    CreatedDate,
                    ModifiedDate
                )
                SELECT 
                    @MatchID,
                    t.GroupId,
                    t.TransIDList,
                    t.CustIDList,
                    t.AssociationType,
                    t.TotalAmount,
                    t.TotalOdds,
                    t.TicketCount,
                    t.CustCount,
                    'GroupBetting' AS DetectionType,
                    t.RuleScore,
                    @BettypeID,
                    @BetID,
                    @Betteam,
                    @ScoreDiff,
                    @SportType,
                    @IsLive,
                    NOW(),
                    NOW()
                FROM TempCompleteGroups t;
                
                Table: CTSMatchMonitorRuleGroupBetting
                Primary Key: ID (auto-increment)
                Unique Index: (MatchID, GroupID, IsLive)
            end note
            
            :Mark Transactions as Processed;
            note right
                -- Extract all SequenceIDs from TransIDList
                CREATE TEMPORARY TABLE TempSequenceIDs AS
                SELECT DISTINCT SequenceID
                FROM CTSMatchMonitorStaging
                WHERE FIND_IN_SET(
                    SequenceID, 
                    (SELECT GROUP_CONCAT(TransIDList) 
                     FROM TempCompleteGroups)
                );
                
                -- Update staging table
                UPDATE CTSMatchMonitorStaging
                SET IsProcessed = 1,
                    ProcessedDate = NOW(),
                    ProcessedBy = 'RuleGroupBetting'
                WHERE SequenceID IN (
                    SELECT SequenceID FROM TempSequenceIDs
                );
                
                -- Get affected row count
                SELECT ROW_COUNT() AS ProcessedCount;
            end note
            
            :Create Audit Log;
            note right
                -- Insert audit record
                INSERT INTO CTSMatchMonitorAuditLog (
                    MatchID,
                    RuleType,
                    ProcessedCount,
                    GroupCount,
                    TotalAmount,
                    MaxSequenceID,
                    IsLive,
                    ProcessDate,
                    ProcessDuration
                )
                VALUES (
                    @MatchID,
                    'GroupBetting',
                    (SELECT COUNT(*) FROM TempSequenceIDs),
                    (SELECT COUNT(*) FROM TempCompleteGroups),
                    (SELECT SUM(TotalAmount) FROM TempCompleteGroups),
                    @MaxSequenceID,
                    @IsLive,
                    NOW(),
                    TIMESTAMPDIFF(MILLISECOND, @StartTime, NOW())
                );
            end note
            
            :Clean Up Temp Tables;
            note right
                DROP TEMPORARY TABLE IF EXISTS TempCompleteGroups;
                DROP TEMPORARY TABLE IF EXISTS TempSequenceIDs;
            end note
            
            :Return Success;
            note right
                SELECT 
                    'Success' AS Status,
                    @MatchID AS MatchID,
                    (SELECT COUNT(*) FROM ...) AS GroupCount,
                    (SELECT COUNT(*) FROM ...) AS ProcessedTickets
            end note
        }
        
        :SP Execution Complete;
    }
    
else (no)
    :No Results to Save;
    note right
        This can happen if:
        - No associations detected
        - All associations filtered out
        - Round 1 & 2 found nothing
        
        Not an error, just no fraud found
    end note
endif

partition "=== WRITE LOG ===" {
    :WriteLogSentryIfError("ProcessRuleGroupBetting");
    
    :Check for Errors;
    note right
        Check MatchProcesses for issues:
        
        var matchProcessNotValid = MatchProcesses
            .Where(x => x.RoundNumber == 2 
                     && x.ReprocessMatches.IsNotNullOrEmpty());
        
        This identifies:
        - Round 2 items that still need reprocessing
        - Unresolved associations
        - Potential infinite loop
    end note
    
    if (Has Errors?) then (yes)
        :Log to Sentry;
        note right
            Utilities.LogSentryInfo(
                ServiceName: "Match Monitor Process Rule GroupBetting Service",
                FunctionName: "ProcessRuleGroupBetting Error",
                Data: matchProcessNotValid,
                IsError: true
            );
            
            Logged Information:
            - MatchID
            - RoundNumber = 2
            - ReprocessMatches (what still needs processing)
            - Original MatchInfo
            - Association detection results
            
            Purpose:
            - Debugging
            - Identify patterns needing improvement
            - Alert for manual review
        end note
    else (no)
        :No Errors;
    endif
}

partition "=== SLEEP ===" {
    :Thread.Sleep(MatchMonitor_SleepTimes);
    note right
        Sleep Duration: 100ms (typical)
        
        Purpose:
        - Prevent database overload
        - Allow other processes CPU time
        - Throttle processing rate
        - Maintain system stability
        
        Trade-off:
        - Slower total processing time
        - But better resource utilization
        - Prevents deadlocks
        - Allows concurrent operations
    end note
}

:Match Processing Complete;

note right
    ================================================
    COMPLETE FLOW END (Per Match)
    ================================================
    
    This flow runs for EACH match in parallel
    Example with 50 matches and 4 threads:
    - Thread 1: Processes 13 matches sequentially
    - Thread 2: Processes 13 matches sequentially
    - Thread 3: Processes 12 matches sequentially
    - Thread 4: Processes 12 matches sequentially
    
    All 50 matches complete → Continue to Clean phase
end note

note right : ALL MATCHES COMPLETE

partition "=== CLEAN UP OLD DATA ===" {
    :CleanTransRuleGroupBetting(isLive, maxSequenceID);
    
    :Database SP Execution;
    note right
        Database: CTS_DataCenter (MySQL)
        SP: CTS_MatchMonitor_RuleGroupBetting_Clean
        
        Input Parameters:
        -----------------
        @IsLive = 1
        @MaxSequenceID = 12346678
    end note
    
    partition "Clean SP Logic" {
        :Calculate Retention Date;
        note right
            SET @RetentionDate = DATE_SUB(NOW(), INTERVAL 7 DAY);
            
            Keep data for 7 days:
            - For audit purposes
            - For investigation
            - For data recovery
            - For debugging
            
            After 7 days: Safe to delete
        end note
        
        :Delete Old Processed Transactions;
        note right
            DELETE FROM CTSMatchMonitorStaging
            WHERE IsLive = @IsLive
                AND PoolType = 1  -- GroupBetting Pool only
                AND IsProcessed = 1  -- Only processed transactions
                AND SequenceID <= @MaxSequenceID  -- Up to current batch
                AND ProcessedDate < @RetentionDate;  -- Older than 7 days
            
            Example:
            Today: 2024-11-19
            RetentionDate: 2024-11-12
            Delete: Transactions processed before 2024-11-12
            
            Typical Delete Count: ~10,000 - 50,000 rows per run
            
            Performance:
            - Uses index: idx_staging_main
            - DELETE in batches if too many rows
            - Minimal lock time
        end note
        
        :Get Deleted Count;
        note right
            SELECT ROW_COUNT() AS DeletedRows;
            
            Returns: Number of rows deleted
            Example: 25,437 rows deleted
        end note
        
        :Log Clean Operation;
        note right
            INSERT INTO CTSMatchMonitorCleanLog (
                PoolType,
                IsLive,
                DeletedRows,
                MaxSequenceID,
                RetentionDate,
                CleanDate
            )
            VALUES (
                1,  -- GroupBetting
                @IsLive,
                ROW_COUNT(),
                @MaxSequenceID,
                @RetentionDate,
                NOW()
            );
        end note
        
        :Optimize Table (if needed);
        note right
            -- Only if large delete
            IF ROW_COUNT() > 50000 THEN
                OPTIMIZE TABLE CTSMatchMonitorStaging;
            END IF;
            
            Purpose:
            - Reclaim disk space
            - Rebuild indexes
            - Improve query performance
            
            Note: Can be slow, so only for large deletes
        end note
        
        :Return Success;
    }
    
    :Clean Complete;
}

:Return Success to Controller;

stop

note right
    ===================================================
    COMPLETE & CLEAN FLOW SUMMARY
    ===================================================
    
    **What Happened:**
    
    1. ✅ Merged Round 1 & Round 2 results
    2. ✅ Removed duplicate groups
    3. ✅ Assigned sequential GroupIDs
    4. ✅ Calculated fraud scores
    5. ✅ Inserted into result table (CTSMatchMonitorRuleGroupBetting)
    6. ✅ Marked staging transactions as processed
    7. ✅ Created audit logs
    8. ✅ Logged errors to Sentry (if any)
    9. ✅ Cleaned up old processed data (7+ days)
    10. ✅ Optimized database (if needed)
    
    **Key Tables Updated:**
    
    - CTSMatchMonitorRuleGroupBetting (INSERT)
      → Fraud detection results
      
    - CTSMatchMonitorStaging (UPDATE)
      → IsProcessed = 1, ProcessedDate = NOW()
      
    - CTSMatchMonitorStaging (DELETE)
      → Old processed transactions (7+ days)
      
    - CTSMatchMonitorAuditLog (INSERT)
      → Audit trail
      
    - CTSMatchMonitorCleanLog (INSERT)
      → Clean operation log
    
    **Performance Metrics:**
    
    - Processing Time: ~100-500ms per match
    - Parallel Threads: 4 (configurable)
    - Batch Size: 1000 tickets (configurable)
    - Sleep Time: 100ms between matches
    - Clean Frequency: Every run
    - Retention Period: 7 days
    
    **Error Handling:**
    
    - All errors logged to Sentry
    - Transaction rollback on failure
    - Retry logic for database deadlocks
    - Graceful degradation
    
    **Downstream Impact:**
    
    - Results available for:
      → Match Monitor Web Page
      → Classification Jobs
      → Reports & Analytics
      → Investigation Tools
      
    - Triggers:
      → Customer classification updates
      → Alert notifications
      → Report generation
end note

@enduml

